Program: Great Lives
Title: Dickie Bird on the life of Sir Leonard Hutton
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b06r5d07
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 11 Dec 2015
Harold 'Dickie' Bird, now retired but one of our best known cricket umpires champions the life of Sir Leonard Hutton. According to Dickie, this Yorkshireman is one of the greatest opening batsmen of all time, who made history by becoming the first professional England captain. Joining him, the Sunday Times cricket correspondent and author Simon Wilde. Matthew Parris is the presenter. The producer is Perminder Khatkar. Show less